        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 10 at 6:14PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 613 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of Robbinsville, or 4 miles west of Town Of
Santeetlah, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fontana Lake, Stecoah, Robbinsville, Fontana Village, Tapoco,
and Lake Santeetlah.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
western North Carolina.</instruction>
